      "side": 1,
      "message": "`iavf_tx_prepare()` can now consume packets without producing descriptors via the new `drop_one` paths. If a call only drops packets, `n_enq` is nonzero but `n_desc` remains zero, so this block does not subtract `n_enq` from `n_left`. The retry path then advances `buffers` by `n_enq` while `n_left` still includes the already-freed packets, which can later free/report the wrong range.\n\nCan we advance `buffers`/`n_left` for any consumed packets independently from the `n_desc` descriptor enqueue path?",
      "revId": "99dcf3799bfda71d4c102e47afb6d6298e2f7113",
